cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CC 

This paper deals with network coding and erasure channels, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses delay in transmitting packets, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SI) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses martingale bounded differences, which is a technique commonly used in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
